"He did mention from time to time that you were in good health, my
dear. You must tell me some day of his last moments. Poor Christopher;
I was very fond of him."

"Sir John Orme knows perfectly well that I have never sung a note;
I saw the knowledge in his face. I shall take good care never to visit
him again."

"You see, madam, it is a long journey, and I ought to start
immediately. My mother has been moved into a small private hospital;
she wants to see me at once."

"My request is this, that if Kate is not on board the Hydra you will cease to persecute her, you will
return to your normal state of health, you will believe that she is,
what in truth she is, your cousin who was Kate Bouverie."
